author: Cape Cod Times sports@capecodonline.com
title: School roundup: Partosan leads Canalmen sweep over D-R
text: Posted Oct. 7, 2015 at 10:06 PM By Cape Cod Times Posted Oct. 7, 2015 at 10:06 PM » Social News BOURNE - Senior Miranda Partosan had another strong all-around performance as the Bourne Canalmen volleyball team continued its winning ways with a 3-0 victory over Dighton-Rehoboth. Partosan recorded seven aces, 12 service points and six kills as Bourne (8-2) won 25-18, 26-24, 25-8. The Canalmen improved to 7-2 in the South Coast Conference. Junior Nicole Gresh also had a strong match for the Canalmen with six aces, 16 service points and six kills. Junior Zoe Slade chipped in with five kills for Bourne and Leah Hidenfelter was a defensive force with 20 digs. The Canalmen are back in action this evening when they travel to Old Rochester in a key SCC match. Barnstable 3, Bridgewater-Raynham 2: The Red Raiders rebounded from a loss to top-ranked Andover on Tuesday with a 25-12, 25-15, 25-19 win over the Trojans in Hyannis. Madison Sollows led the way for Barnstable (9-1) with 12 kills while Michaela Cornwall added 11 kills and six digs and Riley James had eight kills. Ashley McCarthy (17 assists) and Caroline Brodt (16 assists) spread the offense around, with Sarah Higgins leading the Red Raiders at the service line with 10 service points. Jen Peacock added seven points at the line. Barnstable, the No. 3 team in the state, hosts Newton North, the No. 2 team in the state, on Friday. HIGH SCHOOL FIELD HOCKEY Falmouth 2, Nauset 0: Junior Ericka Meissner scored both Clippers’ goals and classmate Molly Duff-Still earned her third shutout in a victory in Falmouth. Meissner scored both goals in the opening half, knocking home a pass from sister Alexia, a senior captain, with 15:23 to go in the frame. Meissner doubled the lead for Falmouth (4-1-2, 2-1 Atlantic Coast League) with 7:26 left in the first half off an assist from senior MaryAlyce Bevacqua. Duff-Still used two big saves to earn her third shutout and got strong defensive support from junior Kate Hamilton, sophomore Rachael Curtis, senior captain Hannah Callahan and senior Emma Underdah. Dighton-Rehoboth 3, Bourne 2: Carly LaCasse had a goal and an assist and the Canalmen gave the South Coast Conference’s first place team all it could handle before falling in Bourne. After losing 5-0 to D-R early in the season, Bourne (6-3-1, 3-3-1 SCC) was in the game throughout, with Donia Siroonian scoring from LaCasse in the first half. The Canalmen trailed 2-1 at the break but LaCasse scored the equalizer unassisted just four minutes into the second half. D-R answered with the game-winner with 20 minutes remaining. Shannon Hurley excelled defensively for Bourne in defeat. Two more golf squads qualify: Sandwich and Falmouth both clinched a berth in the South Section Division 2 golf qualifier being played October 19 at Easton Country Club. The Blue Knights have been a fixture in the tournament since 2004, having qualified each year since then. Wednesday they beat Dartmouth to earn the berth with a 9-4 record. Falmouth returns to the qualifier following Wednesday’s win over Martha’s Vineyard. The Clippers sport an 8-4 record with three more matches on their schedule. By Cape Cod Times
